
7 Rules to get rich
--------------------

1. Budget rule : ( 50 - 30 - 20 Rule )

    50% is for needs ( like rent, recharges, groceries etc.. )
    30% is for wants ( like travelling, movies etc.. )
    20% is for savings ( invest )
    
2. Home buying rule : ( 3 - 20 - 30 Rule )

   3 means 3 times of your annual income

      Ex:- Annual salary is 6,00,000 x 3 years = 18,00,000
            18lakh is the home buying amount 

   20 means that we should have 20% of house value as
       down-payment before going for Home loan

   30 means that our home loan emi should be below 
        30% of the monthly salary

3. Car buying rule : ( 20 - 4 - 10 Rule )
   
    20 means that we should have 20% of car value as
       down-payment before going for car loan
  
    4 means car loan tenure should be 4 years or below 4
      years

    10 means car expences( EMI, maintance etc.. ) should 
       be below 10% of monthly salary for every month

[ Note : Always buy a car when the car price is below 
              of your annual Income ]
   
4. Phone rule :
 
    phone buying amount should be 2% of annual income
    Ex:  6,00,000 x 2% =12,000
          12,000 is the phone buying amount

5. Credit card rule :
    
    we should use 30% or below of credit card limit
    Ex: if the card limit is 1,00,000
         then we should use 30,000 or below 30,000

6. Rule of 72 :

    Rule of 72 is used to estimate the no.of years to
         double the amount for rate of interest

    formula:-  72/( rate of interest ) = years
    
    Ex:- 72/24 = 3

           rate of interest is ---> 24
                    no.of years --->  03
[ Note : This works only for compound interest. ]

